{"id":332689,"link":"https://chinadigitaltimes.net/chinese/2014/02/global-voices-乌克兰撤销短命的反抗议「独裁法」/","date":"2014-02-09T03:45:22Z","modified":"2014-02-09T03:45:22Z","title":"Global Voices | 乌克兰撤销短命的反抗议「独裁法」","content":"<p><div><img alt=\"What the new anti-protest laws meant for Euromaidan protesters at a glance. Translated infographic from Den daily by Euromaidan PR, used with permission. \" src=\"http://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/infografika_zakon1_transl4.jpg\" width=\"584\" height=\"365\"></p>\n<p>这张信息图表一目了然地指出，对于Euromaidan抗议群众来说，新通过的反抗议法意味着什么。此图表来自Den daily，由Euromaidan PR翻译，授权使用。</p>\n</div>\n<p><b>更多乌克兰#Euromaidan相关新闻，请见全球之声特别报导：<em><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/ukraines-euromaiden-protests/\">Ukraine&#8217;s #Euromaidan Protests</a></em></b></p>\n<p>乌克兰国会于2014年1月28日，表决通过撤销具争议的「<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://globalvoicesonline.org/2014/01/17/ukraine-stifles-freedom-of-speech-peaceful-protest-with-new-law/\">独裁法</a>」11条中的9条。所谓的「独裁法」，是国会12天前才通过的法案，意在遏止国内目前持续进行的Euromaidan抗议活动。</p>\n<p>然而，乌克兰人与国际社会看来对这个结果仍十分不满。尽管总理阿扎罗夫（Микола Азаров）与内阁于同一天请辞，抗议群众依然在国内好几座城市街头抗争，反对派领袖也表示，如果无法满足最关键的要求，<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-25900267\">抗议会一直持续下去</a>。1月28日星期二稍早，阿扎罗夫提出请辞，官方声明中写道：</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>为了创造社会与政治之间更大的和解可能性、为了冲突能和平解决，我已做出个人决定，请总统同意我辞去总理之位。</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/ChristopherJM/\">Christopher Miller</a>是乌克兰最著名的英文报纸Kyiv Post的编辑， 他报导了国会表决过程，并在<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/ChristopherJM/status/428120439928279040\">推特上留言</a>：</p>\n<blockquote lang=\"en\">\n<p>361 lawmakers of 412 in session hall today voted to cancel 9 of the repressive laws passed on Jan. 16. Communists didn&#8217;t vote. <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23ukraine&#038;src=hash\">#ukraine</a></p>\n<p>— Christopher Miller (@ChristopherJM) <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/ChristopherJM/statuses/428120439928279040\">January 28, 2014</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote lang=\"en\">\n<p>国会共412位议员里，今天有361位赞成取消1月16日通过的压制性法律。共产党员未投票。#ukraine</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>一直密切关注乌克兰抗议活动的美国记者<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/randomdijit/\">Jake Turk</a><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/randomdijit/status/427938693593067520\">评论说</a>：</p>\n<blockquote lang=\"en\">\n<p>Too little too late? Yanukovych says he&#8217;ll scrap the antiprotest laws. <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://t.co/kaqhOHv8Dl\">http://t.co/kaqhOHv8Dl</a> via <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/RFERL\">@RFERL</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Ukraine&#038;src=hash\">#Ukraine</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Euromaidan&#038;src=hash\">#Euromaidan</a></p>\n<p>— Jake Turk (@randomdijit) <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/randomdijit/statuses/427938693593067520\">January 27, 2014</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote lang=\"en\">\n<p>为时已晚否？亚努科维奇说他会废除反示威法。<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://t.co/kaqhOHv8Dl\">http://t.co/kaqhOHv8Dl</a> via <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/RFERL\">@RFERL</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Ukraine&#038;src=hash\">#Ukraine</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Euromaidan&#038;src=hash\">#Euromaidan</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Euromaidan组织者的「官方英语公关」网站Euromaidan PR<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://euromaidanpr.wordpress.com/2014/01/29/the-price-of-freedom/\">报导</a>：</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>乌克兰人珍视自己的自由，「独裁法」导致大规模愤慨且激烈的抗议。国会刚才已撤销了11条法律中的9条，但是，这些压制性法律的创始元老，以及那些歪曲表决结果的人，都在假装一切十分正常：死去的六位民众还活着、失踪的数十位民众没有失踪、没有上百人遭逮捕，也没有两千人受伤。政府打算「特赦」那些为了维护自己完整自由权利而站出来的民众，好像他们是恶棍一样。</p>\n</blockquote>\n<div><img alt=\"Calculating the price of freedom; image by MaidanSOS, used with permission.\" src=\"http://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/dictatorship.jpg\" width=\"584\" height=\"468\"></p>\n<p>自由的代价电子表格：乌克兰人迫使政府撤销「独裁法」付出的代价。来源为Euromaiden PR。图片：MaidanSOS，授权使用</p>\n</div>\n<p>然而，在1月29日，有消息传总统亚努科维奇尚未签署使系争法律无效的撤销案。推特用户如France 24记者<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/gullivercragg/\">Gulliver Cragg</a>便<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/gullivercragg/status/428644657002602496\">警告</a>：</p>\n<blockquote lang=\"en\">\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23ukraine&#038;src=hash\">#ukraine</a> Yanukovych has NOT signed the cancellation of the anti-protest laws, which I&#8217;m told means they are still in force</p>\n<p>— Gulliver Cragg (@gullivercragg) <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/gullivercragg/statuses/428644657002602496\">January 29, 2014</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote lang=\"en\">\n<p>#ukraine亚努科维奇还没签署反示威法的撤销案，有人告诉我这样意味着这些法律依然有效。</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>BBC Global News编辑<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/OS1954/\">Olexiy Solohubenko</a>也<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/OS1954/statuses/428629159162937344\">补充</a>：</p>\n<blockquote lang=\"en\">\n<p>Not looking good, no amnesty vote in <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Ukraine&#038;src=hash\">#Ukraine</a> and Yanukovych hasn&#8217;t signed the bill revoking anti-protest laws. Stalemate again.</p>\n<p>— Olexiy Solohubenko (@OS1954) <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/OS1954/statuses/428629159162937344\">January 29, 2014</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote lang=\"en\">\n<p>情况不妙，<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Ukraine&#038;src=hash\">#Ukraine</a>没有表决特赦，亚努科维奇也还没签署反抗议的撤销案。再次陷入僵局。</p>\n</blockquote>\n<div>校对：Fen</div>\n<p><span><span>作者 <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://globalvoicesonline.org/author/danica-radisic/\" title=\"文章导读 Danica Radisic\">Danica Radisic</a></span> · <span>译者 <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://zh.globalvoicesonline.org/hans/author/ameli/\" title=\"文章导读 Ameli\">Ameli</a></span></span>  · <span><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://globalvoicesonline.org/2014/01/29/ukraine-rolls-back-short-lived-anti-protest-dictatorship-laws/\" title=\"阅读原文  en\">阅读原文  en</a></span> · <span><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://zh.globalvoicesonline.org/hans/2014/02/09/13158/#comments\" title=\"则留言\">则留言 (0) </a></span><br /><span><span>分享: </span> <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.hemidemi.com/user_bookmark/new?title=%E4%B9%8C%E5%85%8B%E5%85%B0%E6%92%A4%E9%94%80%E7%9F%AD%E5%91%BD%E7%9A%84%E5%8F%8D%E6%8A%97%E8%AE%AE%E3%80%8C%E7%8B%AC%E8%A3%81%E6%B3%95%E3%80%8D&#038;url=http%3A%2F%2Fzh.globalvoicesonline.org%2Fhans%2F2014%2F02%2F09%2F13158%2F&#038;description=&#038;via=sticker\" title=\"HEMiDEMi\"><span>HEMiDEMi</span></a> · <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://myshare.url.com.tw/index.php?func=newurl&#038;url=http%3A%2F%2Fzh.globalvoicesonline.org%2Fhans%2F2014%2F02%2F09%2F13158%2F&#038;desc=%E4%B9%8C%E5%85%8B%E5%85%B0%E6%92%A4%E9%94%80%E7%9F%AD%E5%91%BD%E7%9A%84%E5%8F%8D%E6%8A%97%E8%AE%AE%E3%80%8C%E7%8B%AC%E8%A3%81%E6%B3%95%E3%80%8D\" title=\"MyShare\"><span>MyShare</span></a> · <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.shouker.com/%22%20onclick=20js=document.createElement%20(\" title=\"Shouker\"><span>Shouker</span></a> · <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.facebook.com/share.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fzh.globalvoicesonline.org%2Fhans%2F2014%2F02%2F09%2F13158%2F\" title=\"facebook\"><span>facebook</span></a> · <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"